# Bower Font Usage Rules

Bower is the McKinsey display typeface (--mds-font-display). Its usage is strictly limited.

## Allowed Usage

Bower may ONLY be used when ALL conditions are met:

1. Display sizes only -- Use ONLY with display tokens (display-1 through display-6)
2. Weight 500 or 700 only -- Never 300 or 400.
3. Minimum size 2.75rem (44px) -- This is display-6. Never use Bower below this size.

### Exception: Application Name in Top Banner

The application name/logo in the top navigation banner may use Bower at a minimum size of 1.5rem (24px), with weights 500 or 700. This is the ONLY exception to the 2.75rem minimum rule.

Example:
```css
.app-logo {
  font-family: var(--mds-font-display);
  font-size: 1.5rem; /* Minimum for app name only */
  font-weight: var(--mds-font-weight-bold); /* 700 */
}
```

## Prohibited Usage

Bower must NEVER be used for:

- Data or quantities -- Numbers like $2.4M, 148, 94%. Use McKinsey Sans (--mds-font-body) instead.
- Dashboard widget titles -- Section headers like Recent Projects. Use McKinsey Sans.
- Headings smaller than 2.75rem -- heading-2 through heading-6 are too small for Bower.
- Body text, labels, or captions -- Always use McKinsey Sans.
- Table content -- All table text uses McKinsey Sans.
- Navigation links or buttons -- Always use McKinsey Sans.

## What to Use Instead

For all non-display text, use McKinsey Sans (--mds-font-body).

GOOD - Bower for large display text:
  font-family: var(--mds-font-display)
  font-size: var(--mds-font-size-display-3) 3.5rem 56px
  font-weight: var(--mds-font-weight-medium) 500

GOOD - McKinsey Sans for page titles:
  font-family: var(--mds-font-body)
  font-size: var(--mds-font-size-heading-3)
  font-weight: var(--mds-font-weight-bold)

GOOD - McKinsey Sans for data values:
  font-family: var(--mds-font-body)
  font-size: var(--mds-font-size-heading-2)
  font-weight: var(--mds-font-weight-bold)

BAD - Bower at heading-5 size (1.75rem below 2.75rem minimum):
  font-family: var(--mds-font-display)
  font-size: var(--mds-font-size-heading-5)

BAD - Bower at weight 400:
  font-family: var(--mds-font-display)
  font-weight: var(--mds-font-weight-regular)

BAD - Bower for data values:
  font-family: var(--mds-font-display)
  font-size: var(--mds-font-size-heading-2)

## Quick Reference

Display text at or above 2.75rem: --mds-font-display (Bower), weights 500 or 700
Application name in top banner: --mds-font-display (Bower), minimum 1.5rem, weights 500 or 700 (ONLY exception)
Page titles and headings: --mds-font-body (McKinsey Sans), weights 500 or 700
Widget and section titles: --mds-font-body (McKinsey Sans), weights 500 or 700
Data values and quantities: --mds-font-body (McKinsey Sans), weight 700
Body labels captions: --mds-font-body (McKinsey Sans), weights 400 or 500
Table content: --mds-font-body (McKinsey Sans), weights 400 or 500
Buttons and navigation: --mds-font-body (McKinsey Sans), weight 500
